---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home" description="What if the laws of physics are mathematically inevitable? A framework deriving 63+ physical constants from division algebra geometry.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-950/20 to-gray-950"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-20 pb-16 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white leading-tight mb-6">
        What if the laws of physics are<br class="hidden sm:block" />
        <span class="text-brand-400">mathematically inevitable?</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Perspective Cosmology asks: what happens when an observer is embedded inside a mathematical object?
        The constraints of self-observation force division algebras &mdash; whose dimensions (1, 2, 4, 8)
        determine spacetime geometry, gauge symmetries, and coupling constants. From these structures alone,
        with zero free parameters, the framework derives dozens of physical constants.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-gray-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10 leading-relaxed">
        12 match measurements to better than 10 parts per million.
        14 predictions failed.
        We estimate a <strong class="text-gray-300">25-40% chance</strong> this is real physics.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/explore" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-brand-600 hover:bg-brand-500 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Explore Predictions
          <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/publications/math" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-gray-600 hover:border-gray-400 text-gray-300 hover:text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Read the Math
        </a>
        <a href="/skeptics" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-gray-600 hover:border-gray-400 text-gray-300 hover:text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Why Be Skeptical
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What It Is -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-16 pb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-500 rounded-full"></span>
      What It Is
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
      Perspective Cosmology is a speculative mathematical framework that starts from a single question: <em class="text-white">what is the minimum structure required for observation to exist?</em> The answer turns out to require division algebras &mdash; four special number systems (dimensions 1, 2, 4, 8) that are the only ones where division always works. From those algebras and a consistency principle, the framework derives two integers: crystal dimension n<sub>c</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;11 and defect dimension n<sub>d</sub>&nbsp;=&nbsp;4. Everything else &mdash; the Standard Model gauge group, three generations of fermions, 3+1 spacetime, quantum mechanics, Einstein's equations, and 63+ physical constants &mdash; follows from those two numbers alone.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
      This is amateur work, built with AI assistance over 370+ sessions. It has not been peer-reviewed. We estimate a 25&ndash;40% probability it captures genuine physics.
      <a href="/publications/executive-summary" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300 ml-1">Read the full executive summary &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Where's the Math -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-8 pb-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-500 rounded-full"></span>
      Where's the Math?
    </h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
      The formal derivations live in the <a href="/publications/math" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Mathematical Foundations</a> paper, which builds from axioms through theorems to predictions with full proof chains. For a guided 30-minute evaluation, start with the <a href="/publications/physicist-summary" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Physicist Summary</a>. The <a href="/publications/technical-summary" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Technical Summary</a> covers every derivation chain and all 63+ predictions in one document.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
      For interactive exploration: the <a href="/explore/algebra" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Division Algebra</a> page walks through how dimensions &#123;1, 2, 4, 8&#125; generate the framework's key numbers. The <a href="/explore/catalog" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Framework Catalog</a> maps every prime to a physical constant and catalogues all 17 crystallization types. The <a href="/explore/derivations" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Derivation Chain Viewer</a> lets you trace any prediction back to its axioms step by step.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
      Every numerical claim is backed by a SymPy verification script &mdash; <a href="/verify" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">browse them here</a>, or clone the repo and run them yourself. The <a href="/explore" class="text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300">Prediction Explorer</a> lets you filter all 63+ predictions by precision, domain, and derivation status.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Three-Column Section -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <!-- Column 1: What We Claim -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-brand-500 rounded-full"></span>
          What We Claim
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-400 mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>SM gauge group derived from first principles</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-400 mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Fine structure constant to <strong class="text-white">0.0006 sigma</strong> (dressed)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-400 mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Weinberg angle sin&sup2;&theta;<sub>W</sub> to <strong class="text-white">0.00 sigma</strong> (dressed)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-400 mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Dark matter mass prediction: <strong class="text-white">5.11 GeV</strong></span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-400 mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Lithium-7 problem solved</strong> (BBN/3 from division algebra)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-brand-400 mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">No magnetic monopoles</strong> (topological, not inflation)</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Column 2: Why You Should Doubt It -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent-yellow rounded-full"></span>
          Why You Should Doubt It
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-yellow mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Author is amateur with AI assistance</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-yellow mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Building blocks aren't special (Monte Carlo)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-yellow mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Most predictions are post-hoc</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-yellow mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Could be sophisticated numerology</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-yellow mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>4 irreducible assumptions remain</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-yellow mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>CC magnitude gap unsolved</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Column 3: Why It Might Be Real -->
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-accent-green rounded-full"></span>
          Why It Might Be Real
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-300">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>9 blind predictions succeeded (<strong class="text-white">P ~ 2.5e-7</strong>)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Derives structure, not just numbers</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">736+</strong> verification scripts (99.8% pass)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>14 failures + 3 retractions documented honestly</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Only <strong class="text-white">4 assumptions</strong> for ALL of physics</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-0.5">-</span>
            <span>Concrete falsification criteria</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Highlight Section: 3 Results Most Worth Checking -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-950/50 to-gray-900 border border-brand-900/50 rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-8 text-center">The 3 results most worth checking</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <!-- Alpha -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-mono font-bold text-brand-400 mb-2">1/&alpha;</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Fine structure constant</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-950/60 rounded-lg p-4 mb-3">
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Predicted</div>
            <div class="font-mono text-white text-lg font-semibold">137.035999<span class="text-brand-400">177</span></div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Measured: 137.035999177(21)</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-2">15211/111 + 3-loop rational corrections</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-accent-green font-semibold text-sm">0.0006 sigma from measurement</div>
          <a href="/explore" class="text-xs text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300 mt-2 inline-block">View derivation chain &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <!-- Weinberg -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-mono font-bold text-brand-400 mb-2">sin&sup2;&theta;<sub>W</sub></div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Weinberg angle</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-950/60 rounded-lg p-4 mb-3">
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-1">Predicted</div>
            <div class="font-mono text-white text-lg font-semibold">0.23122</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Measured: 0.23122(4)</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-2">28/121 &minus; &alpha;/(4&pi;&sup2;)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-accent-green font-semibold text-sm">0.00 sigma from PDG</div>
          <a href="/explore" class="text-xs text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300 mt-2 inline-block">View derivation chain &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <!-- Omega_m -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-mono font-bold text-brand-400 mb-2">&Omega;<sub>m</sub></div>
          <div class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">Matter density</div>
          <div class="bg-gray-950/60 rounded-lg p-4 mb-3">
            <div class="font-mono text-white text-sm">63/200</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">= 0.315</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-accent-green font-semibold text-sm">EXACT match to Planck</div>
          <a href="/explore" class="text-xs text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300 mt-2 inline-block">View derivation chain &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-500 text-sm mt-8">
        All three use only the integers &#123;4, 7, 11&#125; &mdash; the spacetime dimension n<sub>d</sub> = dim(H),
        the imaginary octonion dimension Im(O) = 7, and the crystal dimension n<sub>c</sub> = 1 + 3 + 7 = 11. Zero free parameters.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats Bar -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">736+</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Verification Scripts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">99.8%</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Pass Rate</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">14</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Documented Failures</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
        <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">4</div>
        <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Irreducible Assumptions</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer Tagline -->
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 text-center">
    <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-400 italic">
      "25-40% chance this is genuine physics.
    </p>
    <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-white font-semibold mt-1">
      100% chance the math is worth checking."
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8">
      <a href="/skeptics" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-700 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors">
        Read the honest assessment
        <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
